<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width">
    <link rel="apple-touch-icon" sizes="180x180" href="images/fav/apple-touch-icon.png" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="images/fav/favicon-32x32.png" sizes="32x32" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="images/fav/favicon-16x16.png" sizes="16x16" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="images/fav/favicon.ico">
    <link rel="manifest" href="images/fav/manifest.json">
    <link rel="mask-icon" href="images/fav/safari-pinned-tab.svg" color="#5bbad5">
    <meta name="theme-color" content="#ffffff">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/main.css">
    <script src="js/jquery.min.1.12.4.js"></script>
    <script src="js/modernizr.cssmediaqueries.js"></script>
    <!--page title-->
    <title>Multi Language Site Template</title>
</head>

<body>
    <div class="page">
      <h1>SASS RTL/LTR Template</h1>
      <h3>What does it do?</h3>
      <p>This template works a skeleton for creating web interface with dual direction, you will need to compile once and use the same scss files to style the page.<br>Just follow the simple guidelines and your work will be done in not time.</p>

      <h3>Features</h3>
      <p>
        - Ability to add more than one language.<br>
        - browserSync integration that enables auto refresh of the browser upon saving html/scss/js files.<br>
        - Cool mixins included.<br>
        - Easy to read and understand scss file structure.<br>
        - Added autoprefixer support.
      </p>

      <h3>How to use ?</h3>
      <p>- Start by defining the language that you are going to use.</p>
        <h1>Click on the interface local you want to preview/debug/test :</h1>
        {{#each this}}
            <a href="/{{this.outputfolder}}">{{this.languageName}}</a><br>
        {{/each}}
    </div>
    <div class="footer"></div>
    <div class="overly">
        <div class="box action-class"></div>
    </div>
    <script src="js/js.js"></script>
</body>

</html>
